    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-28T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-28T15:00:00-05:00" n="624"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d624">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.01/63: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-28T14:00:00-06:00"
                            >January 28, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. <persName corresp="#p_AL2">Luis Anderson</persName> informs me that he expects
                    to arrive at New York aboard steamship <hi rend="italic">Toloa</hi> February 7th
                    as confidential agent with broad powers of General <persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                        >Max Martínez</persName> to obtain recognition by the United States of
                    present regime in Salvador. He stated that Congress of Salvador will assemble on
                    February 1st and inaugurate former Vice President <persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                        >Martínez</persName> as President on the pretext that the previous incumbent
                    deserted the country. In his arguments <persName corresp="#p_AL2"
                        >Anderson</persName> would present to the Department copies of testimonials
                    by foreign diplomats at San Salvador stating their conviction that <persName
                        corresp="#p_MH1">Martínez</persName> was not connected with <hi
                        rend="italic">coup d’état</hi> of December 3d. <persName corresp="#p_AL2"
                        >Anderson</persName> is concerned at possibility of higher Department
                    officials refusing to receive him. I have refrained so far from discussing
                        <persName corresp="#p_AL2">Anderson</persName> visit with Costa Rican
                    officials. Above text telegraphed to American Legation San Salvador.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
